1
00:00:45,550 --> 00:00:49,200

2
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:52,300
Lee Doo Hak, put your hands up and get on your knees.

3
00:00:52,300 --> 00:00:53,740
Let go!

4
00:00:57,410 --> 00:00:59,490
Don't move!

5
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:06,440
♫  Will I be able to come to you again?  ♫

6
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:08,550
Just stop now, Hyung.

7
00:01:08,550 --> 00:01:10,990
Everything is over.

8
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:13,780
It was you, as expected.

9
00:01:14,980 --> 00:01:17,880
Let's stop now.

10
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:19,750
If I stop,

11
00:01:21,020 --> 00:01:23,170
will you carry out...

12
00:01:23,170 --> 00:01:25,640
my sentence in my place?

13
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:28,840
Just like I how I carried out yours–

14
00:01:31,310 --> 00:01:33,550
Let the hostage go.

15
00:01:33,550 --> 00:01:37,770
I can really shoot you, Hyung!

16
00:01:38,910 --> 00:01:42,000
♫  I can't figure it out  ♫

17
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,760
 Hyung! Please save me.

18
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:46,670
 If you do this for me just this once,

19
00:01:46,670 --> 00:01:48,770
 I will take responsibility for your life!

20
00:01:48,770 --> 00:01:49,880
 No,

21
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:52,130
 I will devote my life to becoming successful,

22
00:01:52,130 --> 00:01:53,650
 and I'll give you all I have.

23
00:01:53,650 --> 00:01:55,730
 You can't take my child away!

24
00:01:55,730 --> 00:01:57,760
 Mom! I'm sorry!

25
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:07,260
♫  It's such a useless thing to say  ♫

26
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:12,330
♫  It's over already  ♫

27
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:20,720
♫  But I can't hide it  ♫

28
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:22,830
♫  My longing for you erupts  ♫

29
00:02:22,830 --> 00:02:24,680
No!

30
00:02:34,330 --> 00:02:36,450
No!

31
00:02:37,610 --> 00:02:39,260
♫  Will I be able to come to you again?  ♫

32
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:41,500
Hyungnim!

33
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:43,530
Doo Hak!

34
00:02:44,740 --> 00:02:52,030
♫  Trembling eyes, they're even more sorrowful  ♫

35
00:02:52,030 --> 00:02:59,820
♫  Above the rough sky, my heart floats away  ♫

36
00:02:59,820 --> 00:03:01,800
Hurry up and find him!

37
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:07,660
♫  Only your name is engraved like this  ♫

38
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,440

39
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:13,360

40
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,650
Hey!

41
00:03:14,650 --> 00:03:16,660
Hey, sit down. Sit down!

42
00:03:16,660 --> 00:03:18,550
Don't you hear me? Sit down!

43
00:03:18,550 --> 00:03:20,650
Are you crazy?

44
00:03:20,650 --> 00:03:22,360
Have you lost your mind?

45
00:03:26,470 --> 00:03:27,870
What happened?

46
00:03:27,870 --> 00:03:29,700
Did you find him?

47
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,910

48
00:03:32,910 --> 00:03:35,370
I asked if you found him!

49
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:39,200
We couldn't find him.

50
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:41,790
Well...

51
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:45,690
It appears he's drifted far into the ocean.

52
00:03:48,610 --> 00:03:50,390
D*mn it!

53
00:03:51,390 --> 00:03:53,000
Find Doo Hak!

54
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,210
Hurry up and find Doo Hak, you b*stard!

55
00:03:55,210 --> 00:03:56,480
Did...

56
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:58,690
Did Hyung Doo Hak really die?

57
00:03:58,690 --> 00:04:01,050
I asked you if he died!

58
00:04:04,790 --> 00:04:07,100
Please find him...

59
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:10,710
The ocean would be too cold for him.

60
00:04:11,460 --> 00:04:21,580

61
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:37,850
Why must it be when it's cold like this?

62
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:40,590
Gosh, darn it.

63
00:04:40,590 --> 00:04:43,360
I didn't think I would go back.

64
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:49,330
I thought that even if I did return, I would return confidently as a boss.

65
00:04:50,620 --> 00:04:53,030
But we're back to being nobodies.

66
00:04:53,030 --> 00:04:55,850
Hey, you b*stard! Who says we're just nobodies?

67
00:04:55,850 --> 00:04:57,200
Although it was just a moment,

68
00:04:57,200 --> 00:05:00,480
we were core members of the council who united all gangs in the country.

69
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:03,340
Did we do that by fighting?

70
00:05:03,340 --> 00:05:05,160
They just joined us as it was profitable.

71
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:07,170
You're so stupid.

72
00:05:07,170 --> 00:05:10,250
Fighting takes skills, and money also needs skills.

73
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:13,190
How do you think Silla united the three kingdoms?

74
00:05:13,190 --> 00:05:17,160
Kim Chun Chu (king) did it through business, while Kim Yu Sin (general) used his sword.

75
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:20,840
Doo Hak and Hyung Joo did the business, while you and I are the muscle.

76
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,950
So it was half business and half muscle.

77
00:05:22,950 --> 00:05:26,040
We united the gangs using both.

78
00:05:27,060 --> 00:05:29,130
Listening to you like this, you're right.

79
00:05:29,130 --> 00:05:34,300
But even in muscle, didn't Hyung Doo Hak do everything?

80
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:38,610
No matter how much dirty work the subordinates do, history only records the bosses.

81
00:05:38,610 --> 00:05:40,300
Isn't that right, Hyung Joo?

82
00:05:40,300 --> 00:05:45,100
Let's go quietly, instead of reminding me of the one who isn't here.

83
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:47,180
This b*stard.

84
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:50,570
Hey! Do you think I want to talk like this?

85
00:05:50,570 --> 00:05:55,630
I keep being reminded of that dead one if I stay still while heading to jail.

86
00:05:55,630 --> 00:06:01,790
If I don't talk this nonsense, I feel I'll go crazy from being reminded of him!

87
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:05,690
Why the heck are you crying?

88
00:06:05,690 --> 00:06:10,500
No matter what I do or say,

89
00:06:11,250 --> 00:06:13,900
I keep thinking of Hyung Doo Hak.

90
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:17,040
Gosh, you stupid b*stard.

91
00:06:18,470 --> 00:06:21,590
Darn it, darn it!

92
00:06:25,230 --> 00:06:27,900

93
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:29,800
Cheol Woong.

94
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:32,190
Happy birthday!

95
00:06:32,190 --> 00:06:34,070
Thank you.

96
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:43,500
All right. Happy birthday, and congratulations on coming up to Seoul.

97
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:44,720
Thank you, Father.

98
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:48,380
You should have come back sooner! You lack nothing.

99
00:06:49,730 --> 00:06:53,500
All right. Was it fun working near your hometown?

100
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:58,250
Whenever I had time at holidays, I dropped by the school I used to go to with Hyung Doo Hak

101
00:06:58,250 --> 00:07:01,200
and also the house we used to live in.

102
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,860
What about Jung Shin?

103
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:04,190
Why is she so late?

104
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:07,270
Did you tell her to join us for dinner?

105
00:07:07,270 --> 00:07:09,560
Yeah, that's strange. She said she was coming.

106
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:12,370
She shows her face once a year for your birthday,

107
00:07:12,370 --> 00:07:14,600
but I guess she forgot it this year.

108
00:07:24,470 --> 00:07:25,810
Hello?

109
00:07:25,810 --> 00:07:27,770
Director Go?

110
00:07:27,770 --> 00:07:30,750
Didn't Boss say anything to you?

111
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:32,440

112
00:07:32,440 --> 00:07:34,590
You know this is wrong, don't you?

113
00:07:34,590 --> 00:07:37,950
Why is she suddenly like this?

114
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:40,060
Please tell Boss to wait just a little bit.

115
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:43,430
I feel I will have to put an end to this once and for all.

116
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:46,490
She probably won't have the leisure to come this year.

117
00:07:46,490 --> 00:07:48,200
Excuse me?

118
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:51,010
Did something happen to Jung Shin?

119
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:55,960
- Hey, Jung Shin! 
 - I'm sorry I'm late.

120
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:59,120
It's been a while. I'm sorry I'm late.

121
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:01,550
All right, you should take a seat.

122
00:08:03,730 --> 00:08:05,640
But are you all right?

123
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:06,890
Did something happen?

124
00:08:06,890 --> 00:08:08,420
Have you supposedly a problem?

125
00:08:08,420 --> 00:08:09,840
"Problem"?

126
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:10,890
I don't.

127
00:08:10,890 --> 00:08:14,370
The problem would be that business is going all too well.

128
00:08:14,370 --> 00:08:17,030
Oh, and this is your gift.

129
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:19,520
Gosh, you didn't have to.

130
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:20,980
You're the only gift I need.

131
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:23,420
Oh, why are you so cheesy?

132
00:08:23,420 --> 00:08:24,990
Thanks.

133
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:29,070
All right. We should all make a toast.

134
00:08:29,070 --> 00:08:32,190
For Cheol Woong's birthday and for his success.

135
00:08:33,090 --> 00:08:34,140
Congrats!

136
00:08:34,140 --> 00:08:35,300
Thank you, Mother.

137
00:08:35,300 --> 00:08:38,070
- Congrats. 
 - Thanks.

138
00:09:19,430 --> 00:09:21,940
Ahjumma, what brings you all the way here?

139
00:09:21,940 --> 00:09:23,440
Hey.

140
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:26,130
I had dinner plans near here.

141
00:09:26,130 --> 00:09:29,330
I just dropped by after I finished.

142
00:09:29,330 --> 00:09:31,070
How are you?

143
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:32,710
Well, yes.

144
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:35,330
Jung Shin, you, too?

145
00:09:35,330 --> 00:09:36,920
Mother.

146
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:40,670
I should have visited you more often. I'm sorry.

147
00:09:42,610 --> 00:09:44,430
You should come inside. It's been a while.

148
00:09:44,430 --> 00:09:46,180
Have some tea with us before you leave.

149
00:09:46,180 --> 00:09:48,580
No, it's all right.

150
00:09:48,580 --> 00:09:52,320
These are side dishes you like so you should eat them.

151
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:57,490
Also, whenever you have time, drop by.

152
00:09:57,490 --> 00:10:00,170
Yes. I'll make sure to visit.

153
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:05,600
At least if I get to see your face, I feel a bit better.

154
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:10,610
Happy birthday.

155
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:14,150
I was a bit sad that I couldn't see you every year I dropped by,

156
00:10:14,150 --> 00:10:17,400
but somehow, this time I was lucky.

157
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,270
Have you dropped by before?

158
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:24,360
I usually just returned right after seeing my parents.

159
00:10:27,820 --> 00:10:29,330
But since I returned to Seoul,

160
00:10:29,330 --> 00:10:32,040
I will visit you from time to time.

161
00:10:33,830 --> 00:10:36,890
Yes, all right. Thanks.

162
00:10:36,890 --> 00:10:39,350
Thanks a lot.

163
00:10:43,190 --> 00:10:44,770
I'll be going.

164
00:10:44,770 --> 00:10:46,620
Yes, get home safely.

165
00:10:46,620 --> 00:10:48,850
Please drive safely.

166
00:11:06,020 --> 00:11:07,320
Let's go inside.

167
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:10,600
Actually, I have to go.

168
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,600
What?

169
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,240
Already?

170
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:14,940
You should eat before you go.

171
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:16,960
Yes, have a cup of tea with us before you go.

172
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:19,810
No, it's already too late.

173
00:11:19,810 --> 00:11:20,920
All right then.

174
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,500
- Are you really leaving? 
 - Yes.

175
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:24,510
See you. I'll call you later!

176
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:34,800
Let's go inside.

177
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:38,730
Then have a good night.

178
00:11:40,820 --> 00:11:42,140
Hey.

179
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:45,390
Congratulations on returning to Seoul.

180
00:11:54,570 --> 00:11:56,200
Come inside.

181
00:11:59,510 --> 00:12:01,800
How did you know it was me?

182
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:03,600
Since I mentioned something about Jung Shin,

183
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:05,900
it's obvious you would ask me about it.

184
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:08,370
Intelligence work is gathering facts,

185
00:12:08,370 --> 00:12:12,510
but reading people is the first step to intelligence work.

186
00:12:13,930 --> 00:12:16,770
You must be preparing for a business trip to Japan.

187
00:12:16,770 --> 00:12:18,460
That's right.

188
00:12:18,460 --> 00:12:21,550
It'll appear to ordinary people as a usual business trip to Japan.

189
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:25,100
It seems something really important.

190
00:12:26,070 --> 00:12:30,590
You can always ask Team Leader Oh, if you want info on Jung Shin.

191
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:33,440
I don't want to do that.

192
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:38,930
Jung Shin is... cornered due to problems with shares in her film company.

193
00:12:38,930 --> 00:12:43,400
She will probably get kicked out soon with only a few dollars to her name.

194
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:51,030
Have you still not changed your mind about pulling out your shares?

195
00:12:51,030 --> 00:12:55,150
If your mind hasn't changed, Mom, my mind won't change, either.

196
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:59,200
Then was it right to spend company money without permission for Film Academy or whatever?

197
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,190
How many times must I tell you?

198
00:13:01,190 --> 00:13:03,590
I made that investment under their promise

199
00:13:03,590 --> 00:13:06,740
to recommend the best directors and writers to our film company!

200
00:13:06,740 --> 00:13:10,110
I see. Is that so?

201
00:13:10,110 --> 00:13:13,100
Will you argue you're right to the very end?

202
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:15,660
Okay. Director Go.

203
00:13:15,660 --> 00:13:17,450
Yes.

204
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:22,840
Here. Take this.

205
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,990
It's your shares.

206
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,880

207
00:13:34,270 --> 00:13:36,550
You're saying this is my share?

208
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:39,570
Yes. That's your share.

209
00:13:39,570 --> 00:13:41,640
It's half my shares of 400 million won.

210
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:43,950
No. From what I know,

211
00:13:43,950 --> 00:13:48,040
half of your shares in the Gyeonggang region, excluding Gwangju and Jeonnam,

212
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,130
that is my share.

213
00:13:50,130 --> 00:13:52,380
That should amount to at least 2 billion so what's this?

214
00:13:52,380 --> 00:13:57,100
Two billion? Give me a break.

215
00:13:57,100 --> 00:14:01,170
Director Go, break it down so she gets it.

216
00:14:01,170 --> 00:14:03,060
Y-Yes.

217
00:14:04,830 --> 00:14:06,800
So the thing is,

218
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:12,330
it's true you own 50% of Boss' shares in Gyeonggang region, Branch Manager.

219
00:14:12,330 --> 00:14:13,860
But since I spent all my life

220
00:14:13,860 --> 00:14:18,610
going through all hard times at the start, Boss said I should have my shares, too.

221
00:14:18,610 --> 00:14:26,200
So Boss gave me 90% of the shares in Gyeonggang region.

222
00:14:29,070 --> 00:14:34,670
So when we do the math, well, half of Boss' shares of 10%

223
00:14:34,670 --> 00:14:36,810
is 5%. That is your share.

224
00:14:36,810 --> 00:14:40,480
It came to exactly 200 million won.

225
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:43,270
- Do you really expect me to believe this? 
 - Goodness.

226
00:14:43,270 --> 00:14:45,120
Are you saying it's not true?

227
00:14:47,550 --> 00:14:51,200
Look at this. We even have a contract we signed together!

228
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:54,370
If this is really Director Go's shares, I will change my last name.

229
00:14:54,370 --> 00:14:57,430
This is clearly prejudice! Isn't this too much!

230
00:14:57,430 --> 00:14:59,410
You're the one who is being too much!

231
00:14:59,410 --> 00:15:02,160
- Mom! 
 - "Mom"?

232
00:15:02,160 --> 00:15:07,210
Although you became my adopted daughter, you originally agreed on your knees to live as my maid!

233
00:15:07,210 --> 00:15:09,400
Are you a goldfish that you already forgot?

234
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:13,200
How dare you argue with me?

235
00:15:15,020 --> 00:15:17,210
I gave you this due to the time we've spent together

236
00:15:17,210 --> 00:15:19,560
so you won't go around begging for food.

237
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:23,130
You choose to pay the rent for this office or to leave.

238
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:25,530
I'm done with you so get lost!

239
00:15:29,510 --> 00:15:32,190
Let me ask you just one thing.

240
00:15:32,970 --> 00:15:36,390
Was I a maid or a daughter?

241
00:15:39,230 --> 00:15:45,100
Let me ask you one thing, too. Was I your master or your mom?

242
00:15:47,290 --> 00:15:50,510
I won't leave the film industry.

243
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:51,900
Gosh...

244
00:15:52,830 --> 00:15:55,260
That's what you want.

245
00:15:58,810 --> 00:16:01,540
Branch Manager, Branch Manager!

246
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:03,450
Aigoo!

247
00:16:03,450 --> 00:16:05,510
Don't do this.

248
00:16:05,510 --> 00:16:08,760
Just get on your knees and beg for forgiveness!

249
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:13,670
Although she speaks coldly like that, do you know how much she loved you?

250
00:16:13,670 --> 00:16:16,240
You're telling me to go back to living as a maid?

251
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:19,960
You can be her servant for a long time, Director Go.

252
00:16:20,990 --> 00:16:26,130
And just wait and see... who will survive in this film industry.

253
00:16:26,130 --> 00:16:28,980
B-B-Branch Manager!

254
00:16:28,980 --> 00:16:32,040
Gosh, that girl, seriously!

255
00:16:34,940 --> 00:16:38,050
Well... Father.

256
00:16:39,110 --> 00:16:41,130
Could you help Jung Shin a little bit?

257
00:16:41,130 --> 00:16:43,580
Do you want to help her?

258
00:16:43,580 --> 00:16:45,030
Yes.

259
00:16:45,030 --> 00:16:46,670
Then help her.

260
00:16:46,670 --> 00:16:50,280
However, you are an adult now.

261
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:53,640
If you want to help the one you love, do it with your own hands.

262
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:56,250
As a man, shouldn't you do that?

263
00:16:56,920 --> 00:16:59,620
What is your heart?

264
00:16:59,620 --> 00:17:02,790
If you can't forget her, then give your all to get her.

265
00:17:02,790 --> 00:17:05,350
If you can't do that, forget her.

266
00:17:05,350 --> 00:17:07,790
I never forgot your mother,

267
